    <step order="2" name="Audit existing memo">Read existing memo (likely 115 lines per commit `4a877b1e`). Verify coverage of: (a) each §10 criterion; (b) ADR-013 (refined) citation; (c) BFF AI extraction assessment cross-reference; (d) one-time retroactive scope statement; (e) R3-feature specifics (endpoint, DTO, what changed). Note gaps.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Inspect R3 feature surface">Briefly read `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs` to confirm what shipped: endpoint path, request DTO (likely contains `attachments: List&lt;AttachmentDto&gt;`), text-content handling. Do NOT modify code.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Fill memo gaps">Amend (do not rewrite) the memo to close §10-criterion gaps. Each amendment 1-3 sentences, evidence-cited, scoped to R3 attachment feature. Confirm one-time-retroactive scope statement is present and prominent.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Cross-link">Ensure R3 lessons-learned.md references the memo (one line). Ensure R4 spec NFR-02 entry and/or CLAUDE.md Decisions Made cross-links the memo. Do NOT touch root CLAUDE.md.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify acceptance">Confirm memo satisfies all NFR-02 acceptance from R4 spec.md: (a) published; (b) answers §10 decision criteria; (c) explicitly scoped to R3 (one-time, no precedent). Cross-links resolve.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update R4 TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 002 from 🔲 → ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document deviations">If anything deviated, record in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/` for R4 lessons-learned.</step>
  </steps>

